Autonomy, Jupiter Fund, 3i Group May Be Active: U.K., Irish Equity Preview

-- B y   J o h n   S i m p s o n   a n d   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 
2011-08-19T06:53:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-18/autonomy-jupiter-fund-3i-group-u-k-irish-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
that may have unusual share-price changes in U.K. and Irish
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses and prices are from
the last market close.  The FTSE 100 Index sank 239.37 points, or 4.5 percent, to
5,092.23 yesterday. The FTSE All-Share Index sank 4.5 percent,
while Ireland’s ISEQ Index slid 4.4 percent.  3i Group Plc (III)  : Britain’s biggest publicly traded
private-equity firm proposed preliminary terms for 375 million
euros ($536 million) of senior financing for the buyout of Dutch
retailer Action, a person familiar with the situation said. The
shares fell 7.6 percent to 204.3 pence.  Autonomy Corp. Plc (AU/ LN): The U.K.’s second-largest
software maker agreed to be acquired by  Hewlett-Packard Co. (HPQ) , the
world’s biggest computer maker, for $10.3 billion in cash. The
shares fell 8.3 percent to 1,429 pence.  BAE Systems Plc (BA/)  : The U.K. arms company and General
Dynamics Corp. won orders to develop the U.S. Army’s ground
combat vehicles, the Pentagon said late yesterday. BAE Systems
Land and Armaments LP, part of London-based BAE Systems,
received a $450 million contract. The shares dropped 4 percent
to 253.8 pence.  Jupiter Fund Management Plc (JUP)  : The British  fund
manager  that went public last year said first-half net income
tripled as it took in more money from clients and earned higher
management fees. The shares fell 7.7 percent to 196.2 pence.  SABMiller Plc (SAB)  : The brewer is raising $12.5 billion
syndicated loan to back its hostile bid for Foster’s Group Ltd.,
Reuters reported, citing banking sources. SAB shares dropped 6
percent to 2,010 pence.  To contact the reporters on this story:
